 worth trying local classes inside test methods, but those names can get complex due to `$1` issues. Maybe keeping top-level classes is better for clarity.\n\n**Clarifying test class generation**\n\nI noticed the inner helper generates `$InnerWorker`, but doesn't create an associated file or test class, which is fine. \n\nNext, I see that the rule indicates if a class name contains a `$`, I should replace it with \"Inner\" in test class names. So, for `ClosureCleaner$`, the test class should indeed be named `ClosureCleanerTest`. There’s mention that inner classes use `$` but avoid using it for naming.\n\nIt makes sense to keep coverage for each dynamically accessed class in its own dedicated Scala test file under `src/test/scala`. The path looks good, and I need to ensure that top-level tests are public. All checked!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08f9da96dc1f02a20169feb547ce34819f9531bf284448f020\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_rVV4DMWzrUxDZuOslxGu6U6J1Gaz3Zla5mPVMAIgyolQq9IBxOWF4fy3sfprXuuPws6m49MwC0WPTBFwubTcnXv_fUS9ugKHv6dnJn9NGSGl97-PjsSRYOb89KabbNlbMN-CKKuiB_1qRS6uaKgsRjFpb9_8JdwVJ2sZFhi9d18bcysp3ia15IcCl6WUpHrSEdOWh9Vj_Y55cazdxszwZvmx9OO0x9Ed8_TFrxhMqEyXWcTNag1LaIcR6xeB6yXgcBCHERSpJ_sh-lVqw802c5d6QabpwuKCqTgBkEsnijfXW1omxDXVweNqE6x6mMq0GEil-_EP699_xFGz2HqGowBeX9D502XlwTO77K1mVPwsSnuk-FpNG-QB1zBltFIf7rrRgz6BIOV-cyR7fIUyEReahO9TMLbTE-BieXBWJ9QzHBuuqQmNXJ5LyGcvQ6xOQCF9eeGspxRB4thcA5d6GEPWaNSHHtjn6SiSF9q8Ps_00YZa9sOLrmLrLyfX1Dy4Y5EKXnWOREisJzWIEF7yahsb2Ll3yoA8H3l0BWnhVkdRdd6OFEQTaEyqnXJlHczm-3hqgVNGXuTpocV--sBcS5l6-J_AfgKR43ShkYEhjFYKGVrc01nsjkPWRYce0pKlsHd8jnzBeQvB6DUkmnbA8JkIfG7JY3COCTMao-cjM1zWhcIF5xZnhjaQ98o--KnxlGOxmJ58Cx_ysE1KvlHgxNZtMnpD7WgVlkUuMGHwYWngz3i-dczCqF41NSbll_QIz5NyAaNzkiNpWv1FYnl_x4gkJEAuj35k7VAyBgUr2-awBJ9OG1BBZGy1UeJNBKcraotECs5Nqt6wXVBiqUYm5eXP9LwiACMZXk6ImruvYiH2Vf564yVtw_fV1kHz597vp5DaV6AlLOYyCNXFG0JchVa3IYcM3EzV3gl6mkVh6frPPCucvVoFEyW6clScFmxZ3F1qNmLaJNGvGbuKg4OoyA7Dp7OJ_mh8wyKSH_b1Bn_Ml_zsmzhfO9XM8QraZ1V7e