[assistant] Fixed the failing `ClosureCleanerTest` behavior.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - `ClosureCleaner` uses bundled `org.apache.xbean.asm7`.
[assistant] - The test helper classes were being compiled to Java 21 bytecode (`major version 65`).
[assistant] - ASM7 cannot read those class files, so `ClosureCleaner.accessedFieldsOf(...)` silently returned empty field sets.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] - Updated `tests/src/com.twitter/chill_2.13/0.10.0/build.gradle` to compile Scala test classes with Java 8 bytecode:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```groovy
[assistant] import org.gradle.api.tasks.scala.ScalaCompile
[assistant] 
[assistant] tasks.withType(ScalaCompile).configureEach {
[assistant]     scalaCompileOptions.additionalParameters = ['-release:8']
[assistant] }
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] This should allow ASM7 to inspect the test helper classes, making these assertions pass and enabling the non-serializable outer-cleaning path to copy accessed fields correctly.
[assistant-event] text_end
